# boards.local.txt.example  — USER-LOCAL programmer overrides
#
# Tool (PKOB/PICkit) serial numbers are specific to YOUR hardware, so they are not
# shipped in the package. If you have only one programmer connected, you don't need
# this file — the default "Programmer: Auto (single tool)" just works.
#
# If you have TWO OR MORE tools connected and need to pick a specific one, copy this
# file to "boards.local.txt" in the installed platform folder (next to boards.txt):
#   <sketchbook or Arduino15>/packages/dspicArduino/hardware/dspic/<version>/
# Arduino merges boards.local.txt with boards.txt and does NOT overwrite it on update.
#
# Find a tool's serial number in MPLAB IPE, or in MPLAB X's tool properties.
# Then add a menu entry per board (replace the names/serials with your own):
#
#   dspic33ck256mp508.menu.prog.mytool=My CK PKoB (SN 12345)
#   dspic33ck256mp508.menu.prog.mytool.upload.tool_sn=BUR233012076
#
#   dspic33ak128mc106.menu.prog.mytool=My AK PKoB (SN 67890)
#   dspic33ak128mc106.menu.prog.mytool.upload.tool_sn=020085204RYN000728
#
# The new option appears under Tools > "Programmer (PKOB S/N)".
#
# Alternatively (e.g. for arduino-cli / scripts), set the IPE_TOOL_SN environment
# variable to the tool serial before uploading — the upload wrapper honours it.
